SIMPLE: sesamoid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sesamoid
<hw>Ses"a*moid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/
like sesame; <?/<?/<?/<?/<?/ sesame + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form: cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧samo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Resembling in
shape the seeds of sesame.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the sesamoid
bones or cartilages; sesamoidal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Sesamoid bones</b></col>, <col><b>Sesamoid
cartilages</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>small bones or
cartilages formed in tendons, like the patella and pisiform in
man.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sesamoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sesamoid
<hw>Ses"a*moid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A sesamoid
bone or cartilage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sesamoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
